EXECUTED MISSED APPROACH FROM FIRST ILS APPROACH. WHILE RECEIVING 
VECTORS FOR SECOND APPROACH, PILOT ADVISED PEORIA, QUINCY AND ST. LOUIS 
WERE STILL ABOVE MINIMUMS. PILOT REPLIED 'I DON'T WANT TO SPEND THE 
NIGHT IN QUINCY'. DURING SECOND APPROACH CRASHED 2000 FEET SHORT OF 
RUNWAY. CEILING AND VISIBILITY ZERO. 
THE PILOT'S IMPROPER IFR PROCEDURE DURING AN ILS APPROACH IN BELOW 
MINIMUM CONDITIONS, AND THE PILOT'S FAILURE TO PROCEED TO AN ALTERNATE 
DESTINATION. CONTRIBUTING FACTORS WERE THE ADVERSE WEATHER 
CONDITIONS. 
